cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC

The paper deals with the fundamental property of partial orders known as width, and specifically focuses on the width of regular and context-free languages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the lexicographic ordering and information leakage, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
